<h2>Mission</h2>
<p><img src="/images/seancribbs-small.jpg" class="float-left" /> I consider myself a versatile citizen of the Digital Age.  I have been a pianist, software engineer, composer, philosopher, web designer, conductor, singer, teacher, and technology advocate.  I believe in being a well-rounded person with many interests.  Hardly a jack-of-all-trades-master-of-none, I have excelled in many areas, including software design and development, music theory, and choral conducting.</p>
<p>I have a passion for formal aesthetics&#8212;I am committed to beauty in design, music, and software.</p>
<h1>The Real Stuff</h1>
<p>I currently work as a Software Engineer for Basho Technologies, creators of the esoterically-awesome Riak distributed database. I develop primarily in Ruby, Erlang, Python, and JavaScript but have been known to write the occasional C program or Bash script.</p>
<h2>Bio</h2>
<p>A native of Kansas City, I currently live away from my hometown in Lawrence, NJ, with my wife, Elizabeth, and two cats, Fiona and Isolde.</p>


